@JuliaRegistrator register

Regarding the third and final issue: "No licenses detected in the package's top-level folder. An OSI-approved license is required.":

We do have a [license](https://github.com/NREL/GhpGhx.jl/blob/main/LICENSE.md), but there is an executable file in the package that must be governed by that license and it is likely more restrictive than OSI would like to see. This module supports the BSD-3 open source [REopt.jl](https://github.com/NREL/REopt.jl) package for evaluating geothermal heat pumps. Can we get an exception to the OSI-approved license?

